On Wed, 27 Mar 2002 14:03:29 +0100, Thierry Bouche wrote:

>well... there was the idea in fontname that _n_ & _c_ are not equivalent
>(one is for a designed condensed version, and the other one for an
>automatically narrowed one [I may confuse which is which]).

Good idea -- in theory!

In the KB fontname scheme, however, the ready-made (designed) 
Helvetica-Narrow is named "n", whereas the equally ready-made 
Frutiger-Condensed or Univers-Condensed are named "c".  The 
KB scheme simply reflects the original names, and we are now
stuck with it.

